[node name="Level9" type="Node3D"]
editor_description = "Room 09 — Echo Kick. Symmetrical twin corridor past the fork at z=2: LeftFloor/RightFloor are separated by an open gap (no floor, no wall needed — straying into the middle just falls through like any other out-of-bounds drop). WireNodeA (left) and WireNodeB (right) both have to surge within SyncGateLock's sync_window of each other. Press E (EchoKickStation) to bank the Ball's current run as a replaying ghost and reset the Ball to try the other side live. GREYBOX FIRST PASS — corridor length/sync_window are unverified numbers, expect to retune once someone's actually played the timing."

